reviews.text:
I've checked out many capoeira schools, and training with Mestre Foca and Professora Rouxinol has been the best experience by far. Mestre Foca teaches a style that's playful, that emphasizes the importance of seeing your partner, and using cleverness as well as strength to build a beautiful capoeira game. Professora Rouxinol teaches with the same spirit, and brings her expertise as a personal trainer to combine capoeira movement with strength and flexibility conditioning. Watching them play is equally stunning and inspiring. 

The community they've helped build is also incredible. It's like family. I'd highly recommend checking out a class, or an Absolute Beginners series (that's how I got into it, since I knew I'd have a month to learn the ropes before getting in the thick of things.)

The best capoeira school in Brooklyn! Mestre Foca is, hands down, one of the best teachers I've had in any discipline. When I did the intro series nearly eight years ago, I had no idea I'd still be training three to four times a week today, nor that so many lasting friendships would come out of this awesome community.

Best Capoeira!

reviews.text: Here you will learn the traditional Capoeira Angola. Mestre Grande is part of  the second generation of capoeiristas under Mestre Pastinha's lineage. Here you will realize the spirituality is a very important part of the growing process. Mestre Grande teaches in Brooklyn, New York in the same tradition as learned from his Master. We are committed to teach Capoeira Angola based on what our ancestors taught us. As part of the tradition, classes are taught in Portuguese. Love, dignity, freedom, respect, discipline, diversity and non-violence are our principles. It's more like a family outside home. We offer classes to any age - you will see us having classes for 3 years old as well as 80 years old. Capoeira is for men, women, kids and youths. We can all live in harmony. There is no happiness if our brothers/sisters are unhappy. Ubuntu! Saúde & Axé para todos! Viva a Capoeira Angola! Viva Deus do Céu!
This is an amazing group, everyone is family, Mestre Grande is passionate about capoeira and looks after each of his students. Come and learn capoeira whatever your age and your shape!

Centro de Capoeira Angola Filhos de Dunga is a home away from home for me. Mestre Grande and Professor Mel are amazing, loving people and phenomenal instructors in the art form / language / music of Capoeira Angola. It's a great time, it's a great community, a great workout, and a beautiful lesson in culture and love. I highly recommend studying Capoeira at the school.

If you're looking to explore the movement, music, and history of capoeira, then Filhos de Dunga is the place to be. I've been overjoyed with the  opportunity to connect to the roots of a culture that has been passed from master to student for hundreds of years, transmitted to our community by our own Mestre Grande. I am challenged daily (yes, I said daily!) and have experienced enormous personal growth over these almost two years. Come join us!

I promise you definitely will see improvements, whether you are a beginner or advanced student.
